## 10. Watch List: Emerging Infrastructure

**Notion Workers (pre-alpha — do not build against yet)**
Notion Workers is Vercel-hosted compute infrastructure that would allow code to run in response to Notion events without a separate server or cloud function. If it ships as described, it eliminates the "Notion cannot receive inbound webhooks" constraint entirely and makes several OBS → Notion chains significantly cleaner — specifically the local bridge script requirement. No timeline confirmed. Monitor `notion.com/releases` for GA announcement. For anyone building toward Notion partnership track, this is the most important infrastructure development to watch in 2026.

**Notion Markdown API (unverified — verify before building)**
Claimed availability of `GET /v1/pages/{id}/markdown` and `PATCH /v1/pages/{id}/markdown` endpoints. If confirmed, this significantly simplifies programmatic writing to Notion — no more constructing nested JSON block arrays. Would make the ONCE mythology draft → Notion pipeline and the stream recap → Notion pipeline much cleaner. Verify at `developers.notion.com/page/changelog` before building.

